Docker Desktop Installation:- Install Docker from the official docker website and follow the installation guide.
https://docs.docker.com/desktop/install/mac-install/

Docker Desktop Includes:
Docker Engine:-
* A server with long running daemon process "dockerd"
* Manages images and containers.

Docker CLI client:-
* Command Line Interface (docker) to "interact with Docker Server"
* Execute Docker commands to start/stop /... containers

Docker GUI Client:-
* To manage your images and containers with a GUI (Graphical User Interface).
* It is helpful when you don't wants to work with command Line based interface and wants to have nice user friendly UI.




